<TITLE> Bangla Academy honours 17, including Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 26 (bdnews24.com)  Bangla Academy bestowed honorary fellowships on finance minister AMA Muhith and 16 others, including two foreigners, on Saturday. Bangla Academy chairman Kabir Chowdhury said, "To honour those who have contributed more or less for the Bangla language and culture is a part of the academy's regular programme." Muhith told bdnews24.com, "This is an exceptional honour for me. An honour for honouring my own language and mother tongue." The two foreigners are Clinton B Seely, emeritus professor of Bangla language and literature at Chicago University, and Japanese professor Kazuo Azuma, who teaches at Vishwa Bharati University at Shantiniketan in West Bengal, India, and has translated Rabindranath Tagore's songs from Bangla into Japanese. The others fellows are ABM Musa, Amirul Islam, Ataus Samad, Ferdausi Majumder, Akber Ali Khan, Abdus Samad Mandal, Bibi Russel, Mahbubur Rahman, Habibullah Pathan, Rawshan Ara Bachchu, Nurul Islam, Amanul Haque, Imdad Hossain and ABM Abdul Latif Mia. bdnews2
